\i Entry 3 - 
\i0 This is unexpected. While spelunking through the source-code, I started to notice some random looking symbols cropping up. At first I thought it must be a glitches in the unicode table or something, but the symbols aren't in any of character codes that I've seen. The internet doesn't provide any answers either. Perhaps even more strange is what happens when I deleted the spurious code. Every time I push to the repository it gives me some kind of permissions error. I really need to get this sorted soon, operations have ground to a halt, and everyone's looking at me like some kind of idiot for keeping things held up. I'm not one for conspiracies, but I often wonder about the "Security protocols" Antumbra installed on these machines. It could be messing with code repository, or worse, perhaps they are intentionally altering it with encrypted code chunks? But why?
